{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17650081","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17650081"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:09:32+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:09:32+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18388"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18388","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18388"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.36,0.12,0.08,0,0.44]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11106"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74699"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11106","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11106"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18388"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60182"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"9511"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25748"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25751"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74699","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74699"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA patient has sustained a penetrating injury to the knee.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely condition associated with this injury?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Capsule injury","Meniscal tear","Ligament rupture","Intra-articular fracture","Septic arthritis"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient has sustained a penetrating injury to the knee, which places him at high risk for \u003Cstrong\u003Eseptic arthritis\u003C/strong\u003E. The open wound and potential joint involvement necessitates surgical intervention to prevent infection. Septic arthritis is a serious condition that can lead to joint destruction if not promptly addressed.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECapsule injury\u003C/strong\u003E could occur with a penetrating injury, but the primary concern is infection due to the open wound and potential joint involvement.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMeniscal tear\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Eligament rupture\u003C/strong\u003E are possible with knee injuries, but they are less likely to be the immediate concern in the context of a penetrating injury with a high risk of infection.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntra-articular fracture\u003C/strong\u003E A fracture can be seen on an Xray. The primary concern in this scenario remains the risk of infection in the joint space.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Penetrating joint injuries are at high risk for septic arthritis, requiring prompt surgical intervention.","Arthrotomy and lavage are critical in managing penetrating joint injuries to prevent infection and further complications.","Prophylactic antibiotics are essential in preventing septic arthritis following a penetrating joint injury."],"references":["Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2021). Textbook of Orthopaedics, 2e-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Dandy, D. J., \u0026 Edwards, D. J. (2009). Essential Orthopaedics and Trauma E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","MacGregor R, Byerly DW. Anatomy, Bony Pelvis and Lower Limb: Foot Bones. 2023 May 23. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32491379","Ombregt, L. (2013). A System of Orthopaedic Medicine-E-Book: A System of Orthopaedic Medicine-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60182"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18388"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60182","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60182"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-26T15:55:09+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-02T08:25:18+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11106"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74699"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:51:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"34","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/34"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddb4","name":"Orthopaedics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":